source.g: As in the previous question, Ramon’s father developed a fever and cough on April 3. On April 5, Ramon’s father gets tested for COVID-19, and on April 7 he receives positive test results. As a result, Ramon’s father self-isolates beginning on April 8. After 2 days, Ramon drives his father to the hospital on April 10. Now when is the last day of Ramon’s quarantine?
Incorrect. Ramon has to quarantine for 10 days from the date when he last had close contact with his father. April 17 is only 7 days after April 10. He has to stay in quarantine 3 days longer.
Correct. Ramon drove his father to the hospital on April 10, so Ramon’s quarantine ends 10 days later, on April 20.
Incorrect. Ramon has to quarantine for only 10 days from the date when he last had close contact with his father. April 24 is 14 days after April 10.
Incorrect. Ramon has to quarantine for only 10 days from the date when he last had close contact with his father. April 26 is 16 days after April 10.
